   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422599_1833_03_10_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE"/>Edgeworths Town
                  <date when="1833-03-10">March 10 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1833.</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute/>
            </opener>
            <p>I am not sure that I have<lb/>
               a aright in common honesty<lb/>
               to keep possession of the speech<lb/>
               which came enclosed to me<lb/>
               yesterday under cover from<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#SpriT1">Mr. Spring Rice</persName> - because<lb/>
               his own hand has inscribed<lb/>
               it to<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#CaseJ1">J Casey</persName>
               <lb/>
               from his old friend <unclear/>
               <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>But as common honesty<lb/>
               knows seldom suffered<lb/>
               to stand between us and<lb/>
               temptation &amp; there are so<lb/>
               many ingenuous ways of<lb/>
               evading that vulgar virtue<lb/>
               I shall avail myself of<lb/>
               my <hi rend="underline">cover</hi> &amp; keep possession<lb/>
               of my treasure â€” I think<lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422599_1833_03_10_page02.jpg"/>
               is a treasure of good facts<lb/>
               â€” well put â€” and <choice>
                  <orig>unanswera<lb/>
                  ble</orig>
                  <reg>unanswerable</reg>
               </choice> â€” I was exceedingly<lb/>
               gratified (as people usually<lb/>
               are) to see my own opinion<lb/>
               and aperÃ§ues so ably &amp;<lb/>
               incontrovertibly supported<lb/>
               by Experience and <choice>
                  <orig>Arithme<lb/>
                  tic</orig>
                  <reg>Arithmetic</reg>
               </choice> - the mighty two whom<lb/>
               neither Eloquence nor<lb/>
               Rhetoric nor Falsehood<lb/>
               nor Impudence in any<lb/>
               shape even Dan's own, can<lb/>
               overthrow â€”<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>Pray send me a permit<lb/>
               to keep my speech with a<lb/>
               safe conscience<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>Yours truly<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p>I particularly like the speech<lb/>
                  <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422599_1833_03_10_page03.jpg"/>
                  for being unadorned â€”<lb/>
                  Earnestness is the soul of<lb/>
                  real eloquence<lb/>
               </p>
               <p>I beg you to frank the<lb/>
                  letter to<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HillA1" cert="high">A Hill Esq</persName><lb/>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Hazelwood_ENK">Hazlewood</placeName>
                     <lb/>
                     <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Birmingham_ENK">Burmingham</placeName>
                  <lb/>
               </p>
               <p>Letters to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF3">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Wilson</persName> will<lb/>
                  find their way of their<lb/>
                  <hi rend="underline">own accord by habit</hi>
                  <lb/>
                  through your Right Honorable<lb/>
                  Honor<lb/>
                  <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Morgan_422599_1833_03_10_page04.jpg"/>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <date when="1833-03-10"/>10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> March 1833<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss Edgeworth</persName>
                  <lb/>
                  acknowledging receipt<lb/>
                  of speech â€”<lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
                  <addrLine/>
               </address>
            </closer>
